&quot;Lincoln described liberty by a useful analogy: &quot;The shepherd drives the wolf from the sheep's throat, for which the sheep thanks the shepherd as a liberator, while the wolf denounces him for the same act as the destroyer of liberty.&quot; Lincoln made it clear who the sheep was and who the wolf was. It is equally important to recognize who the liberator is.<br>
