<br>
Because they are American, they have the right to protest.  They shouldn't forget, however, that the 'rights' they so value are in truth nothing more than privilages that the founders of this nation shot people for.  Peace is <u>not</u> the natural state of the world, and connot be maintained by inaction.  Every American soldier who dies in this war (keep in mind our death count against Iraq last time was 200-something) could very well be saving the life of 1,000 civilians by preventing even a single terrorist attack  using Iraqi chemical or biological weapons.  It's never a good thing when one must look at the trade-off in lives but, no matter how many feel-good words you say, this does not keep it from being neccessary.<br>
<br>
We live in a new America, and most of the people have not yet realized that we most likely will never again drop below yellow on the 'Terror Scale' because they do not want it to be so.  They must, but sadly do not, realize that playing ostrich with our heads in the sand as regards even the <u>possibility</u> of such strikes is the exact same attitude that allowed Germany to walk into Poland and France in the early 20th century.  Remember that?<br>
<br>
If countless Americans want to rail against military force because it's trendy for Wynona Ryder to tell them to, or because they thought their relatives joined the military for a free scholarship, they have that right.  Every American has the right to be wrong.  No Iraqi has the right to be right, however.  Hopefully, that will change in a week or two.  <br>
<br>
Do not equate Bush with war, however.  The blame for conflict lies on a man who tiptoed around straightforward demands by the UN for him to disarm for 12 years, and the neccessity for Bush to have to stand up and do something about it lies on the leaders of other nations who were willing to let our grandchildren deal with the problem.<br>
<br>
Bush came to a point in history where he could safely play his cards towards re-election, or take a huge risk and end the threat of Saddam.  He does not deserve the outright hatred idiotic liberals throw at him, and it's a shame that their idiocy may cost us the first president we've had with conviction in almost a decade.<br>
<br>
Fuck France. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:#DC143C;font-size:small;">Bungabunga &lt;Heavy Hand&gt;<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->53 Troll Beastlord<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->&quot;Have Gator, will travel.&quot;<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
