<br>
If the French and Germans had united against Saddam is a peacefully disarmament, then this would have all been avoided.  Saddam couldn't have with stood the combined will of the world powers and would have realized that is time for playing games and stalling UN inspectors was up.  In time, he would have destroyed his weapons that he wasn't allowed to have and then been allowed to continue to rule in the way that he has for the last 20  years.  <br>
But that never happened.  France and Germany thought that both Bush and Blair would fold like a cheap deck of cards went he pressure got high enough and they could still continue on with thier  lucrative financial programs with Iraq.  But neither Bush nor Blair stuck thier fingers in the wind to listen what the people with the loudest voices had to say about the matter... they stuck to thier principals.  Like it or not.<br>
<br>
Today people in Afghanistan are free. There is not more family and other privately owned business in the country than ever before.  Women are not being raped in public and men  not being murdered in front of their family because they protested the government.  The Iraqi's will know this freedom soon.  It is unfortunate that the 700,000  that Saddam has murdered in his own country weren't allowed the same freedom.<br>
<br>
We all have the right in the US and the UK to protest.  I happened to get stuck in the first major protest in London last fall.  Here was the make up of the protestors.. the UK Socialist party (i.e. Communism of this era), Muslims extremist in London who openly preach for war to thier people, I am not sure what other name to call this group), peace-nics (those who live in a fantasy world were if we all just love each other everything will be all right), and my favorite... the anti-capitalist professional protestors (the type that would demonstrate against sliced bread if someone told them it was a capitalist plot).  That was about 60% of the people.  The rest were either people like me who made a wrong turn and were stuck for 3 hours, or the London middle class who came out with their wine and cheese just to see what all the noise was about.<br>
<br>
The reason why I mentioned all of those groups, is that they all hate Western government, particularly Bush and Blair.  However, Bush and Blair fighting for relative and prosperity of the western world... and to insure that all of these people will be free to protest again.  <br>
<br>
If at any time you think these terrorist that want to destroy Americans, English, Australians, and everyone else associated with the western world, are not worth dealing with and that we live in a safe and comfortable society.... then down load one of the videos of the 9/11 tragedy... particular the one where the towers fell... and 3,000 were killed.<br>
<br>
I pray for the people of Iraq, and that they will not have to endure and more hardship than they must.<br>
<br>
Sorry to get long winded... but it is good to get some things off of your chest, particularly when you are surrounded by people who talk funny all of the time. <p>Viva la Revelution!! <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
